3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper proposes a novel precoder design for interference alignment, which involves signal processing techniques. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of different decoders in terms of error rate, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization of transmission schemes, which is relevant to computational engineering and science.
